      "description": "Marsh and willow tits of the northern Palearctic — drab but charming birds in brown and white, best told apart by their calls. The Willow Tit excavates its own nest hole in rotten wood, while the Marsh Tit takes over existing cavities. The Siberian Tit is one of the hardiest passerines on Earth, surviving Arctic winters through shivering, food caching, and a remarkably high metabolic rate. In North America the genus includes the chickadees, among the most familiar and beloved backyard birds on the continent.",
